news.title: Lucknow development body to cancel lease of 50 allottees in Transport nagar
news.para: According to LDA officials, the development authority had provided vacant plots to these beneficiaries in 2011 on lease for construction of housing units. However, no construction work has been carried out on these lands.

news.title: No NOC mentioning floor of property issued: Chandigarh to HC
news.para: The court, on Wednesday, had directed the administration to submit the affidavit after petitioners’ claim that the UT had issued an NOC for floor-wise registry and they also submitted details of the certificate issued for that specific property.

news.title: HC stays NCDRC three-year jail order to Supertech's MD, directs Rs 50 lakh be paid to buyer
news.para: The NCDRC order, to the extent that the company's MD is sentenced to 3-year imprisonment, shall remain stayed till the next date of hearing - October 4.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC proposes Rs 41.9 crore property tax waiver for hotels
news.para: According to officials, nearly Rs 41.9 crore of property tax is expected to be waived for the period from February to May. Last year, the BMC had waived property tax of Rs 22 crore for 182 hotels and lodges from April to June 2020 during the first wave.

news.title: Banks, builders pin hopes of a revival on India festival season
news.para: Lenders including SBI, HDFC, Kotak Mahindra Bank have slashed home loan rates by 15-60 basis points to between 6.5 percent and 6.7 percent -- the lowest level in a decade.

news.title: Building sealed in Panchkula over Rs 36 lakh pending property tax
news.para: Gulshan Kumar, zonal taxation officer, MC said that SCO 104-195, owned by Ansal, was sealed after there was no reply from the firm over the property tax default notice.

news.title: Pune: Section of corporators opposes penalty relief for property tax dues
news.para: The move aims at increasing the revenue of the civic administration, it said. The PMC has organised a Lok Adalat on September 25, where 500 cases of tax defaulters would be amicably resolved.

news.title: NGT seeks action on Aravali encroachments
news.para: The court was hearing a petition on Wednesday regarding illegal construction in ‘gair mumkin pahar’ of Aravalis hills in three Haryana districts — Faridabad, Nuh and Gurgaon — and Alwar in Rajasthan. A copy of the order was uploaded on Thursday.

news.title: After 30-year wait, Prayagraj development body begins process to give land to allottees
news.para: Early this month, PDA has come up with this unique scheme, ‘Mission Sangam’, following which the authorities have identified 415 individuals who were allotted land by the PDA but they failed to get the possession for various reasons.

news.title: Casagrand plans for IPO in 2022
news.para: Casagrand plans to strengthen its presence in Bengaluru and will be investing Rs 1,250 crore in the next one year. The company is also looking to enter Hyderabad market with an initial investment of Rs 1,500 crore.

news.title: Construction sites in Noida flout rules, but no action yet: Residents
news.para: The residents alleged they hadn’t received any response from the Uttar Pradesh Pollution Control Board despite several tweets on the violations.

news.title: Chandigarh: Gupta Builders' owners booked in cheating cases running into crores
news.para: All the three cases were registered in the Sector 34 police station. The economic offences wing (EOW) of the UT police is conducting investigations. No arrest has been made so far.

news.title: UltraTech Cement commits to 100% renewable energy usage by 2050
news.para: "As part of this commitment, UltraTech targets to meet 100 per cent of its electricity requirement through renewables sources by 2050," the company said in a statement.

news.title: DHFL approaches Bombay HC to discharge name from CBI prosecution
news.para: The company has challenged a special Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) court order of August 20, which had given partial relief by discharging the interim monitoring committee but had rejected DHFL’s prayer to discharge it from the case.

news.title: I-T searches builders' premises in Mumbai and Pune
news.para: It is learnt that some of these builders have links with senior politicians of the ruling alliance in Maharashtra government.
